## Summary

Fixes #5420. This patch fixes a solver error when constraint expressions contain shift operators whose operands have different bitvector widths. SMT-LIB2 `bvshl`/`bvlshr`/`bvashr` require both operands to have the same bitvector sort, but `ConstraintExprVisitor` passed shift operands to `editSMT()` at their original widths.

## Reproducer

```systemverilog
class AlignedPacket;
  typedef logic [36:0] address_t;
  typedef logic [3:0]  size_t;
  rand address_t address;
  rand size_t    size;
  constraint c_aligned {
    address % (1 << size) == 0;
  }
endclass

module t;
  initial begin
    AlignedPacket pkt = new;
    if (!pkt.randomize()) $stop;
    $display("PASS");
  end
endmodule
```

On master:
```
%Warning: .../include/verilated_random.cpp:642: Internal: Solver error:
  (error "line 11 column 330: Argument size at position 1 has sort (_ BitVec 4)
  it does not match declaration (declare-fun bvshl ((_ BitVec 37) (_ BitVec 37)) (_ BitVec 37))")
```

## Changes

- Added `handleShift()` helper in `ConstraintExprVisitor` that zero-extends the RHS operand via `AstExtend` when narrower than LHS, propagating `user1()` (rand-variable dependency marker) to the new extend node
- Added dedicated `visit(AstShiftL*)`, `visit(AstShiftR*)`, `visit(AstShiftRS*)` overrides that call `handleShift()` instead of falling through to the generic `visit(AstNodeBiop*)` handler

## Test

- Added `test_regress/t/t_constraint_shift_width.{v,py}` -- tests mixed-width shifts in constraints: variable shift amount (37-bit LHS / 4-bit RHS), constant shift amount, and implication with shift

